# Pixolotl — GDD v1.1

> **Godot rework of the Unity kit.** All distances use metres and all ordinary
> timing uses seconds. Pixolotl additionally owns a **local time rate**; rules that
> use it say so explicitly. In-run character leveling is removed: HP is a flat base
> and permanent growth comes from the run's additive HP/ATK/DEF pools.

## Character Overview

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Race | Axolotl |
| Role | Ranged control / temporal zoning |
| Realm | Not Found (origin unknown; not presently in the world pool) |
| HP | 150 |
| Personality | Playful, curious, and slightly out of sync with time. She speaks in fragments as if always half a second behind or ahead. |

The papel picado ghosts are marigold-orange path markers, not ominous spectres.

---

## Visual Design

The runtime currently has the existing Pixolotl character sheets only; the old-project
standalone ghost and bubble sprites are absent from this checkout. Until they are supplied,
the ghost uses the pooled marigold fallback and the bubble uses a rendered **2 m diameter**
fallback matching its collision shape. Core requirements remain external-gill bubble firing,
marigold-orange papel picado afterimages, time-reversal treatment for bubbles, and cyan
active-time feedback during E.

---

## Shared Rule — Local Time Rate

Pixolotl and every bubble she owns simulate using an effective **Local Time Rate**.
The default rate is **1.0**. Their simulation delta is:

```text
actDelta = worldDelta × localTimeRate
```

Thus a rate of **1.5** advances Pixolotl's own simulation by 1.5 seconds for each
world second. The rate applies to her movement simulation, gravity, acceleration,
passive-frame generation, BA interval, reloads, skill cooldowns, active buffs and
debuffs, and every live bubble's movement and lifetime. Input remains real-time.

Future combat-wide bullet time must be composed as a separate world rate plus each
entity's relative local rate; it must not use Godot's global engine time scale. A
future world rate of 0.1 and Pixolotl-relative rate of 5.0 gives her an effective
rate of 0.5 — five times faster than that world while still moving at half her normal
real-time speed.

---

## Passive — Tiempo de Papel Picado

Every **0.3 local-time seconds**, Pixolotl stores a `PapelPicadoFrame` in a circular
buffer of **8 slots**.

| Recorded state | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Position | Shift rewind destination |
| Current HP | Shift's non-destructive heal calculation |
| Movement velocity | Shift's arrival momentum |

Each stored frame creates one translucent marigold ghost at that position. A ghost
fades from 70% alpha toward 30% alpha over **3.2 seconds**, then would hold at 30%.
In normal play the frame is overwritten first; overwriting or consuming it force-fades
the associated ghost over **0.3 seconds** and returns it to the visual pool.

The eight-frame trail places markers every 3 m while Pixolotl moves at her 10 m/s
base speed. The oldest and newest stored markers are up to 21 m apart; her current
position forms the final 3 m of the visible route.

> **Design note:** ghosts are both telegraph and ammunition. Enemies can see the route
> Pixolotl has prepared, but must respect the possibility that she will rewind to any
> remaining point on it.

---

## Basic Attack — Branquias (Gills)

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Magazine | 3 volleys |
| Bubbles per volley | 6 |
| BA interval | 0.3 local-time s |
| Reload | 0.9 local-time s, refill to 3 volleys |
| Damage | 20 per bubble |
| Bubble diameter | 2 m |
| Launch speed | 6 m/s, added to Pixolotl's current world velocity |
| Directional phase | 1.5 local-time s |
| Horizontal brake after phase | 0.15 local-time s to zero X velocity |
| Rising phase | directly upward at 2 m/s |
| Lifetime | 10 local-time s |

Each volley fires all six bubbles simultaneously at these fixed **world-space** angles.
Angles use +X as right and positive Y as up; they never flip with facing direction.

| Bubble | Angle |
|---|---:|
| 1 | 0° |
| 2 | 25° |
| 3 | 65° |
| 4 | 115° |
| 5 | 155° |
| 6 | 180° |

### Bubble state and collision rules

1. For exactly 1.5 local-time seconds, the bubble travels with its launch velocity:
   `angleDirection × 6 m/s + Pixolotl velocity captured at firing`.
2. It then brakes its horizontal velocity to zero over 0.15 local-time seconds and
   transitions to direct upward travel at 2 m/s. All bubbles therefore begin their
   rising phase at the same local-time age, regardless of their launch angle.
3. A bubble cracks and despawns only on Ground or Platform contact, or when its
   10-second lifetime expires. It passes through SoftVolumes and **does not despawn
   when it touches an enemy**.
4. Each bubble keeps a lifetime hit registry: it may damage each target at most once,
   including while retracing its path during Shift. It may continue through other
   enemies that it has not yet hit.
5. Bubbles inherit Pixolotl's current Local Time Rate at every simulation step. E
   therefore speeds all live bubbles immediately; Shift reverses their simulation age.

> **Design note:** Branquias is a broad, low-burst coverage tool. The short directional
> phase spreads bubbles across the lower arena; their shared rising phase forms a
> readable vertical curtain that threatens opponents who jump through prepared ground.

---

## Shift — RANIBOBER (Held Rewind)

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Cooldown | 15 local-time s |
| Requirement | At least 1 stored frame |
| Frames available | Up to 8, newest to oldest |
| Rewind intervals | 0.375 s for jumps 1–3; 0.25 s for jumps 4–8 |
| Arrival damage | 25 |
| Arrival area | centered 3 m × 3 m square |
| Arrival control | Trapped for 1 s |
| Heal | 50% of HP lost since the final rewind frame |
| Recovery | 0.25 s, vulnerable and input-locked |

Shift is a long press. On press, Pixolotl enters Rewind state: she becomes invincible,
cannot move, and every other input is banned. She does not move immediately. At the end
of the first interval she rewinds to the newest stored frame, then consumes and rewinds
to one older frame at each later interval. The 15-second cooldown starts with the first
successful frame jump.

Releasing Shift after at least one frame jump — or consuming all frames — resolves at
the current rewind frame:

1. Pixolotl remains at that frame's position and receives its recorded velocity.
2. She heals `0.5 × max(0, frameHP − currentHP)`, capped at Max HP. Her HP is never
   reduced if the frame recorded less HP than she currently has.
3. All foes in the centered 3 m × 3 m square take 25 damage and receive the existing
   **Trapped** status for 1 second: no self-directed movement or jump, but skills may
   still be cast. This is the counterplay window, not a guaranteed kill.
4. Every live Pixolotl bubble reverses its deterministic simulation age by the same
   frame interval(s) traversed during this Shift. Bubbles retrace their path visually,
   but keep their lifetime target-hit registry.
5. Pixolotl enters a 0.25-second vulnerable recovery. She is no longer invincible and
   cannot move, attack, or cast during this recovery.

If Shift is released before the first frame jump, it cancels without the arrival effect
or cooldown. If the chosen historical position is now invalid terrain, the runtime must
resolve to the nearest valid position before applying the arrival effect.

> **Design note:** RANIBOBER makes the visible frame route dangerous ground. It is both
> a defensive escape and a committed control setup: Pixolotl must expose where she will
> return, while opponents can leave the route, go high, or punish her recovery.

---

## E — SOBRECARGA (Click Local-Time Boost)

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Cooldown | 10 local-time s |
| Local Time Rate while active | 1.5× |
| End condition | 10 frames generated during this activation |
| Maximum duration | 3 real-time s |
| BA and movement | Allowed |
| Shift while active | Banned |

E is a click. On press, Pixolotl's Local Time Rate becomes 1.5 and the burst continues
without holding the key. It ends when it has generated 10 passive frames during this
activation or at the 3-second real-time safety limit — whichever happens first. The
10-frame condition normally ends it after 2.0 real-time seconds because the passive
runs at 1.5×.

While E is active, Pixolotl may move and use Branquias, but she cannot enter Shift.
Every one of Pixolotl's cooldowns — including the active E cooldown — plus reloads,
frame generation, movement simulation, buffs/debuffs, bubble movement, and bubble
lifetimes advances at the 1.5× local rate.

> **Design note:** SOBRECARGA is setup mobility, not a separate damage window. It lets
> Pixolotl lay a denser temporal route and develop a bubble curtain before opponents
> can claim the same ground.

---

## Skill-State Exclusivity

Pixolotl has three input states: Normal, E Active, and Shift Rewind.

| State | Move | BA | E | Shift |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Normal | Yes | Yes | Start | Start if a frame exists |
| E Active | Yes | Yes | Already active | Banned |
| Shift Rewind | No | No | Banned | Continue/release |
| Shift recovery | No | No | No | No |

Only one skill can be active at a time. Tab switching is also unavailable during E,
Shift, or Shift recovery, so a body swap cannot escape their commitments.

