## Decisions log

### v1.1 — Temporal route rework (July 2026)

- Replaced the Unity burst-window kit with a 0.3-second, eight-frame visible route;
  the route is Pixolotl's primary zoning telegraph and rewind resource.
- Replaced straight infinite bubbles with a 1.5-second six-angle launch followed by a
  shared rising phase. This creates lower-ground coverage and readable anti-air space
  without aim-based DPS.
- Made Shift a held, newest-to-oldest rewind with invulnerability only while committed,
  Trapped arrival control, and vulnerable recovery. The route is powerful but visibly
  counterable rather than an untelegraphed teleport.
- Made E a held 1.5× Local Time Rate boost, capped by ten generated frames or 2.5 real
  seconds. This was superseded by the click-activated 3-second rule in v1.2. Local time is an
  extensible combat contract that later supports bullet time.
- Bubble enemy contact does not despawn the projectile; each bubble instead has a
  lifetime per-target hit cap. This preserves field coverage while avoiding repeated
  overlap damage.

### v1.2 — Click boost and universal opening gate (July 2026)

- Changed SOBRECARGA from a held input to a click-activated burst. It remains at 1.5×
  local time but now finishes after 10 generated frames or 3 real seconds.
- Defined the bubble's collision and rendered fallback diameter as 2 m.
- Defined the opening countdown as Arena-owned and universal: ambient spawns, mission
  waves, and boss spawns all wait for its three seconds to complete.

*Last Updated: July 2026 | Version: 1.2*
